page.title: 01Dorking-NE
page.content: This area is on the edge of Dorking Town and also takes in the small communities of West Humble,Pixham and Box Hill.It is easily reached by road and rail and as a result a few large firms have set up offices near the railway station.The{housing}in the area is nearly all low density, shopping facilities are few and the inhabitants are employed either locally or may commute to London.The most important aspect of the area is it's{Natural Beauty.}Much of it is either National Trust land (wooded or grassy slopes) or farmland lying in the gap made by the River Mole through the{North Downs}and by that part of the Downs called Box Hill.The countryside is used by many people seeking{recreation,}walkers,cyclists ,horse riders etc.
